  "text": "Single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) were determined by alignment with reference strains (M. tuberculosis H37Rv accession no. NC_000962.3 or M. canettii cluster A Percy3 [STB-D CIPT140060008 accession no. NC_019950.1]) as described (7; online Technical Appendix 1, wwwnc.cdc.gov/EID/article/20/1/13-0652-Techapp1. pdf). The determination of statistically significant clustering of polymorphic positions was done essentially as described by Croucher et al. [CITATION_1] .",
